<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/f026a9469a0786aebd23772d8fc44b16.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 12 and A = 5 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>137.2</li><li>137.7</li><li>85.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}=\frac{{12}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{12}}{{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{137.16062763314}\approx{137.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={12}^{{2}}+{137.16062763314}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={144}+{18813.037772716}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={18957.037772716}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{18957.037772716}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{137.68455894804}\approx{137.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{5}^{\circ}\approx{85}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

